Sure, the number of delis that sell lox is more than zero (and less than all), but the clue is where one would look for lox. Delis also sell batteries and toilet paper. And if I want to buy a small overpriced package of either, I'll buy them at the deli.

But I wouldn't look for lox at a deli. I'd look for it at a bagel/appetizing store (or a grocery store). Maybe I'm spoiled as a New Yorker, but I'm not getting my bagels at a deli, either. And what's the point of lox without a bagel

